From 30076d84b300c12b3807159a1d0a63f44f2effee Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Hermes Agent <hermes@nousresearch.com>
Date: Tue, 16 Jun 2026 18:55:18 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Add 32-bit (x86/Win32) support for dk.dll
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Phase 1 — Build system:
- dk.vcxproj: Win32 configs now link (lib\x86, dbgeng.lib, C++20, _HAS_STD_BYTE)
- CI: build.yml + release.yml now build [x64, Win32] platform matrix

Phase 2 — Mechanical fixes:
- page.h: PTE64 → PTE rename, sizeof(PTE) instead of hardcoded 8
- page.cpp: ADDR_HEX_WIDTH constant, arch-aware DML links, CR3/page masks
- hexsvg.cpp: SVG row header arch-aware address format
- dk_server.cpp: ImageBaseAddress VT_UI8→VT_UI4 fallback
- All %I64x size_t values safely cast to (unsigned long long)

Phase 3 — Arch-aware dispatch:
- CmdExt: pointer_size() cached via GetPointerSize(), EXT_F_POINTER_SIZE
- HEX_ADDR/WHEX_ADDR/HEX_DATA macros parameterized on pointer size
- is_reg(), dump_regs(), dump_args(), usermode_regs(): x86 register tables
- dk_server.cpp: reg_aliases_x86 table
- page.cpp + memory.cpp: runtime page-table dispatch (AMD64 4-level / PAE 3-level)
- memory.cpp: as_dword command alias for 32-bit sessions

Design doc: dk/docs/32bit-support.md (22 issues, 21 resolved)
